{
  "texts": [
    "Since ζ F [X] ⊆ ζ -1 F [ζ F [X]] is immediate, we begin with ζ F [X] ⊇ ζ -1 F [ζ F [X]].",
    "If ζ F (y) ∈ ζ F [X], then for some x ∈ X, ζ F (y) = {y ′ ∈ S | y ′ ⊑ s y} = ζ F (x) = {x ′ ∈ S | x ′ ⊑ s x}.",
    "Hence y ⊑ s x, which with x ∈ X and Fact 4.2 implies y ∈ X, so ζ F (y) ∈ ζ F [X].",
    "Thus, ζ F [X] ⊇ ζ -1 F [ζ F [X]].",
    "For the required X ′, take X ′ = {Y ∈ (F b) p | Y ⊑ (F b)p X}, so by (⋆), ζ F [X] ⊆ X ′ and hence ζ F [X] ⊆ ζ F [S] ∩ X ′."
  ]
}